_:N858f1bfa66ff4fffa9c4d0d106e08db6 <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Before retiring in 2020, Eleanor Cozens worked in market research and then in international development, where she led or supported programmes for international charities in the UK and abroad.</p>\n\n<p>Her work included developing programme policies relating to eye health and disability and inclusion and the evaluation of health system strengthening initiatives abroad and introduction of new eye health programmes.</p>\n\n<p>This has given Eleanor considerable experience in exploring and understanding different stakeholders’ perspectives, particularly patients and community members.</p>\n\n<p>Eleanor was an active member of the British Medical Association’s patient liaison group from 2009 to 2014 and has been a carer and patient advocate for a family member.</p>\n\n<p>She enjoys using her professional and personal experiences as an NHS user to contribute general patient and public perspectives to the UK NSC’s processes.</p>\n" .
